BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:beb0f6659da5bc28@homeschool-schedule
SUMMARY:Running Session
DTSTAMP:20260709T151000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260802T071500
DESCRIPTION:Week 1 focus: Easy aerobic\n30–40 min comfortable pace — build 
	base\, conversation effort\n\nSession structure:\n• Warm-up (10 min) — Eas
	y jog\, dynamic stretch\, A-skips\n• Main set (25 min) — Intervals or stea
	dy tempo — see weekly focus\n• Strides / accelerations (10 min) — 4–6 shor
	t bursts with full walk-back recovery\n• Cooldown (5 min) — Easy jog or wa
	lk\, stretch calves and hips\n\nInstagram drill library: add links in inst
	agram_drill_library.json or session_themes.json → running.instagramUrls\n\
	nTheme focus: aerobic base\, intervals\, tempo runs\, recovery pace\, socc
	er-specific conditioning
LOCATION:Track / Field / Road
DURATION:PT50M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3281e5ded0822f26@homeschool-schedule
SUMMARY:Yoga / Stretch
DTSTAMP:20260709T151000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260802T073000
DESCRIPTION:Week 1 focus: Post-training recovery\nLonger holds after hard s
	essions\n\nSession structure:\n• Breath & warm (2 min) — Easy nasal breath
	ing\, neck and shoulder rolls\n• Lower body (6 min) — Hip flexor\, hamstri
	ng\, calf\, figure-4 stretch\n• Core & spine (4 min) — Cat-cow\, child's p
	ose\, gentle twist\n• Close (3 min) — Hold any tight area\; slow breath\n\
	nInstagram drill library:\n• https://www.instagram.com/reel/DW_zewYkeet/\n
	\nTheme focus: mobility\, flexibility\, recovery\, hip and hamstring openn
	ess\, breath work
LOCATION:Home
DURATION:PT15M
END:VEVENT
